22TOI%20TECH%20DESK%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Ftechnology%2Ftech-news%2Famazon-india-admits-security-lapses-at-delhi-ncr-warehouse-heres-what-the-company-said%2Farticleshow%2F111274158.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Indian-American%20Couple%20Jailed%20For%20Forcing%20Cousin%20To%20Work%20At%20Petrol%20Pump%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EA%20US%20court%20has%20sentenced%20an%20Indian-American%20couple%20to%20prison%20for%20coercing%20their%20relative%20to%20work%20at%20their%20gas%20station%20and%20convenience%20store%20for%20over%20three%20years%20by%20bringing%20him%20to%20the%20United%20States%20on%20the%20pretext%20of%20helping%20enrol%20him%20in%20a%20school.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHarmanpreet%20Singh%2C%2031%2C%20was%20sentenced%20to%20135%20months%20(11.25%20years)%20in%20prison%20and%20Kulbir%20Kaur%2C%2043%2C%20to%2087%20months%20(7.25%20years)%20by%20the%20court%20that%20also%20asked%20them%20to%20pay%20the%20victim%2C%20his%20cousin%2C%20USD%20225%2C210.76%20(Rs%201.87%20crores%20approximately)%20in%20restitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20couple%20has%20since%20divorced.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20defendants%20exploited%20their%20relationship%20with%20the%20victim%20to%20lure%20him%20to%20the%20United%20States%20with%20false%20promises%20that%20they%20would%20help%20enrol%20him%20in%20school%2C%26quot%3B%20Assistant%20Attorney%20General%20Kristen%20Clarke%20of%20the%20Justice%20Department's%20Civil%20Rights%20Division%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20defendants%20confiscated%20the%20victim's%20immigration%20documents%20and%20subjected%20him%20to%20threats%2C%20physical%20force%20and%20mental%20abuse%20to%20coerce%20him%20to%20work%20long%20hours%20for%20minimal%20pay%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20sentence%20should%20send%20a%20strong%20message%20that%20such%20forced%20labour%20will%20not%20be%20tolerated%20in%20our%20communities%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUS%20Attorney%20Jessica%20D%20Aber%20for%20the%20Eastern%20District%20of%20Virginia%20said%20the%20defendants%20preyed%20on%20the%20victim's%20earnest%20desire%20to%20attain%20an%20education%20and%20improve%20his%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20they%20deprived%20him%20of%20the%20most%20basic%20human%20needs%20and%20robbed%20him%20of%20his%20freedom%2C%20the%20attorney%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20evidence%20presented%20at%20trial%20demonstrated%20that%20in%202018%2C%20the%20defendants%20enticed%20the%20victim%2C%20Singh's%20cousin%20and%20then%20a%20minor%2C%20to%20travel%20to%20the%20US%20from%20India%20with%20false%20promises%20of%20helping%20enrol%20him%20in%20school%2C%20the%20Department%20of%20Justice%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20said%20that%20after%20the%20victim%20arrived%20in%20the%20US%2C%20the%20defendants%20took%20his%20immigration%20documents%20and%20instead%20forced%20him%20to%20provide%20labour%20and%20services%20at%20Singh's%20store%20for%20over%20three%20years%2C%20between%20March%202018%20and%20May%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESingh%20and%20Kaur%20compelled%20the%20victim%20to%20work%20at%20the%20store%2C%20including%20cleaning%2C%20cooking%2C%20stocking%20and%20handling%20the%20cash%20register%20and%20store%20records%2C%20between%2012%20and%2017%20hours%20a%20day%2C%20nearly%20every%20day%2C%20for%20minimal%20pay%2C%20according%20to%20the%20evidence%20presented%20during%20the%20trial.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20used%20various%20coercive%20means%2C%20including%20confiscating%20the%20victim's%20immigration%20documents%20and%20subjecting%20the%20victim%20to%20physical%20abuse%2C%20threats%20of%20force%20and%20other%20serious%20harm%2C%20and%2C%20at%20times%2C%20degrading%20living%20conditions%20to%20compel%20him%20to%20continue%20working%2C%20the%20evidence%20showed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20couple%20left%20the%20victim%20at%20the%20store%20to%20sleep%20in%20a%20back%20office%20for%20days%20on%20multiple%20occasions%2C%20limited%20his%20access%20to%20food%2C%20refused%20to%20provide%20medical%20care%20or%20education%2C%20used%20surveillance%20equipment%20to%20monitor%20the%20victim%20both%20at%20the%20store%20and%20in%20their%20home%2C%20refused%20his%20requests%20to%20return%20to%20India%20and%20made%20him%20overstay%20his%20visa%2C%20according%20to%20the%20evidence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20defendants%20also%20forced%20the%20victim%20to%20marry%20Kaur%20and%20used%20that%20marriage%20to%20threaten%20to%20take%20the%20victim's%20family's%20properties%20or%20falsely%20report%20him%20to%20the%20police%20if%20he%20left.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20evidence%20also%20showed%20that%20Singh%20pulled%20the%20victim's%20hair%2C%20slapped%20and%20kicked%20him%20when%20he%20requested%20his%20immigration%20documents%20back%20or%20tried%20to%20leave.%20On%20three%20different%20occasions%2C%20he%20threatened%20the%20victim%20with%20a%20revolver%20for%20trying%20to%20take%20a%20day%20off%20and%20for%20trying%20to%20leave.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1719374940000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-06%2Fspvid2ig_harmanpreet-singh-kulbir-kaur_625x300_26_June_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Findian-american-couple-jailed-for-forcing-cousin-to-work-at-petrol-pump-5971341%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20US%20court%20has%20sentenced%20an%20Indian-American%20couple%20to%20prison%20for%20coercing%20their%20relative%20to%20work%20at%20their%20gas%20station%20and%20convenience%20store%20for%20over%20three%20years%20by%20bringing%20him%20to%20the%20United%20States%20on%20the%20pretext%20of%20helping%20enrol%20him%20in%20a%20school.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22