ssange%20Pleads%20Guilty%20In%20US%20Court%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EWikiLeaks%20founder%20Julian%20Assange%20pleaded%20guilty%20in%20a%20US%20court%20in%20Saipan%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20AFP%20reporters%20said%2C%20in%20a%20plea%20bargain%20that%20will%20leave%20him%20a%20free%20man%20after%20years%20of%20legal%20drama.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%2052-year-old%20admitted%20to%20a%20single%20count%20of%20conspiracy%20to%20obtain%20and%20disseminate%20national%20defence%20information%20in%20the%20courtroom%20in%20the%20Northern%20Mariana%20Islands%2C%20a%20Pacific%20US%20territory.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGuilty%20to%20the%20information%2C%26quot%3B%20Assange%20said%2C%20later%20joking%20to%20the%20judge%20during%20the%20proceedings%20that%20whether%20he%20is%20satisfied%20%26quot%3Bdepends%20on%20the%20outcome%20of%20the%20hearing%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAssange%20has%20long%20been%20wanted%20by%20Washington%20for%20releasing%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%20of%20secret%20US%20documents%20from%202010%20as%20head%20of%20the%20whistleblowing%20website%20WikiLeaks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20released%20Monday%20from%20a%20high-security%20British%20prison%20where%20he%20had%20been%20held%20for%20five%20years%20while%20he%20fought%20extradition%20to%20the%20United%20States.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20Wednesday%2C%20he%20is%20expected%20to%20be%20sentenced%20to%20five%20years%20and%20two%20months%20in%20prison%2C%20with%20credit%20for%20the%20same%20amount%20of%20time%20he%20spent%20behind%20bars%20in%20Britain.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAssange's%20wife%20Stella%20said%20he%20would%20be%20a%20%26quot%3Bfree%20man%26quot%3B%2C%20thanking%20supporters%20who%20have%20campaigned%20for%20his%20release.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20weren't%20really%20sure%20until%20the%20last%2024%20hours%20that%20it%20was%20actually%20happening%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20BBC%20radio%2C%20saying%20she%20was%20%26quot%3Bjust%20elated%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Northern%20Mariana%20Islands%20was%20chosen%20because%20of%20Assange's%20unwillingness%20to%20go%20to%20the%20continental%20United%20States%20and%20because%20of%20its%20proximity%20to%20Australia%2C%20a%20court%20filing%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20hearing%20is%20done%2C%20Assange%20will%20fly%20to%20Canberra%20in%20Australia%2C%20WikiLeaks%20said%20on%20social%20media%20platform%20X%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20plea%20bargain%20%26quot%3Bshould%20never%20have%20had%20to%20happen.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Australian%20government%20said%20his%20case%20had%20%26quot%3Bdragged%20on%20for%20too%20long%26quot%3B%20and%20there%20was%20%26quot%3Bnothing%20to%20be%20gained%20by%20his%20continued%20incarceration%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E-%20End%20of%20an%20ordeal%20-%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%202010%20Assange%20has%20become%20a%20hero%20to%20free%20speech%20campaigners%20and%20a%20villain%20to%20those%20who%20thought%20he%20had%20endangered%20US%20security%20and%20intelligence%20sources.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUS%20authorities%20wanted%20to%20put%20Assange%20on%20trial%20for%20divulging%20military%20secrets%20about%20the%20wars%20in%20Iraq%20and%20Afghanistan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20indicted%20by%20a%20US%20federal%20grand%20jury%20in%202019%20on%2018%20counts%20stemming%20from%20WikiLeaks'%20publication%20of%20a%20trove%20of%20national%20security%20documents.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20United%20Nations%20hailed%20Assange's%20release%2C%20saying%20the%20case%20had%20raised%20%26quot%3Ba%20series%20of%20human%20rights%20concerns%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAssange's%20mother%20Christine%20Assange%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20carried%20by%20Australian%20media%20that%20she%20was%20%26quot%3Bgrateful%20that%20my%20son's%20ordeal%20is%20finally%20coming%20to%20an%20end.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20former%20US%20vice%20president%20Mike%20Pence%20slammed%20the%20plea%20deal%20on%20X%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bmiscarriage%20of%20justice%26quot%3B%20that%20%26quot%3Bdishonors%20the%20service%20and%20sacrifice%20of%20the%20men%20and%20women%20of%20our%20Armed%20Forces.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20announcement%20of%20the%20deal%20came%20two%20weeks%20before%20Assange%20was%20scheduled%20to%20appear%20in%20court%20in%20Britain%20to%20appeal%20against%20a%20ruling%20that%20approved%20his%20extradition%20to%20the%20United%20States.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E-%20Extradition%20battle%20-%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAssange%20had%20been%20detained%20in%20the%20high-security%20Belmarsh%20prison%20in%20London%20since%20April%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20arrested%20after%20spending%20seven%20years%20in%20Ecuador's%20London%20embassy%20to%20avoid%20extradition%20to%20Sweden%2C%20where%20he%20faced%20accusations%20of%20sexual%20assault%20that%20were%20eventually%20dropped.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20material%20he%20released%20through%20WikiLeaks%20included%20video%20showing%20civilians%20being%20killed%20by%20fire%20from%20a%20US%20helicopter%20gunship%20in%20Iraq%20in%202007.%20The%20victims%20included%20a%20photographer%20and%20a%20driver%20from%20Reuters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20United%20States%20accused%20Assange%20under%20the%201917%20Espionage%20Act%20and%20supporters%20warned%20he%20risked%20being%20sentenced%20to%20175%20years%20in%20prison.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20British%20government%20approved%20his%20extradition%20in%20June%202022%20but%2C%20in%20a%20recent%20twist%2C%20two%20British%20judges%20said%20in%20May%20that%20he%20could%20appeal%20against%20the%20transfer.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20plea%20deal%20was%20not%20entirely%20unexpected.%20US%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20had%20been%20under%20growing%20pressure%20to%20drop%20the%20long-running%20case%20against%20Assange.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Australian%20government%20made%20an%20official%20request%20to%20that%20effect%20in%20February%20and%20Biden%20said%20he%20would%20consider%20it%2C%20raising%20hopes%20among%20Assange%20supporters%20that%20his%20ordeal%20might%20end.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20first%20official%20US%20reax%20to%20the%20plea%20deal%2C%20State%20Department%20spokesman%20Matthew%20Miller%20said%20that%20as%20the%20case%20is%20about%20to%20go%20before%20a%20judge%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20it's%20appropriate%20for%20me%20to%20not%20comment%20on%20the%20matter%20at%20this%20time.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1719360000000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-06%2F4ingcj8_julian-assange_625x300_26_June_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fwikileaks-julian-assange-plea-bargain-hearing-begins-at-us-court-5970631%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20plea%20bargain%20hearing%20for%20Julian%20Assange%20began%20at%20a%20US%20court%20in%20Saipan%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20AFP%20reporters%20said%2C%20in%20a%20final%20legal%20step%20expected%20to%20leave%20the%20WikiLeaks%20founder%20a%20free%20man.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fwikileaks-julian-assange-plea-bargain-hearing-begins-at-us-court-5970631%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fwikileaks-julian-assange-plea-bargain-hearing-begins-at-us-court-5970631%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fwikileaks-julian-assange-plea-bargain-hearing-begins-at-us-court-5970631%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%E2%80%98Confessions%20of%20a%20Good%20Samaritan%E2%80%99%20Review%3A%20Penny%20Lane%20Delivers%20a%20Documentary%20Essay%20on%20Altruism%20and%20Its%20Discontents%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1719360000000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2Fwp-