n-and-trumps-first-2024-debate%2Famp_articleshow%2F111239856.cms%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThursday's%20presidential%20debate%3C%2Fa%3E%20will%20rake%20in%20huge%20sums.%20Yet%20other%20networks%20are%20allowed%20to%20air%20the%20live%20broadcast%20of%20the%20showdown%2C%20setting%20them%20up%20to%20outperform%20CNN%20at%20its%20own%20game.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPresident%20Joe%20Biden%20and%20former%20President%20Donald%20Trump's%20uncharacteristically%20early%20face-off%20is%20notable%20for%20various%20reasons%2C%20namely%20the%20two%20commercial%20breaks%20that%20will%20splice%20up%20the%2090-minute%20debate.%20Presidential%20debates%20have%20historically%20been%20ad-free%2C%20but%20CNN%20is%20offering%20two%20tiers%20of%20advertising%20this%20year%2C%20with%20the%20most%20robust%20package%20costing%20a%20minimum%20of%20%241.5%20million%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.semafor.com%2Farticle%2F05%2F31%2F2024%2Fcnn-seeks-millions-in-debate-ads%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esources%20told%20Semafor%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20CNN%20is%20hosting%20and%20moderating%20the%20debate%20from%20its%20studios%20in%20Atlanta%2C%20other%20networks%20can%20sell%20their%20own%20advertisements%20during%20their%20simulcasts.%20Given%20that%20some%20of%20those%20networks%2C%20like%20Fox%20News%20and%20MSNBC%2C%20typically%20have%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finsiders-react-to-ex-nyt-mark-thompsons-appointment-cnn-ceo-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elarger%20primetime%20audience%20than%20CNN%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20they%20may%20be%20able%20to%20sell%20advertising%20slots%20for%20more%20money%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F2024%2Ftv%2Fnews%2Fcnn-biden-trump-debate-commercial-breaks-ads-1236020209%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EVariety%20reports%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPer%20CNN's%20rules%2C%20networks%20cannot%20plug%20commercial%20breaks%20with%20commentary%20from%20their%20own